ccess, product development and technology to maximize new customer acquisition and ongoing customer retention; Partner with finance, sales and technology to build out the data and analytics tools and processes to ensure proper flow of data to optimize lead generation, qualification and leverage to accelerate pipeline build from the top of the funnel to the bottom; Create the digital foundation and platform for the marketing department overall including the implementation and use of HubSpot and related technologies; grow and upgrade organizational capability in the digital area and seamlessly integrate digital marketing into each marketing program; Partner with the CEO, CFO and sales to create marketing strategies that drive customer understanding of Magnus and Veracross\u2019s highly compelling differentiation from its competitors; Deliver a robust integrated marketing calendar that is aligned with the differing sales cycles and market channels for Magnus and Veracross\u2019s portfolio of products and services that effectively communicates their holistic value proposition and solutions for its customers and a consistent customer experience across the customer journey/lifecycle; Lead brand development and awareness initiatives across all channels including current and future employees working closely with the Director of People; develop and drive the company\u2019s online presence and social media strategy; Evaluate current marketing organization and hire, develop and retain a best-in-class marketing team to support the Company\u2019s growth plans; Establish an annual marketing budget and carefully monitor adherence and ROI; Establish him or herself as the company\u2019s lead evangelist, both internally and externally for the Magnus/Veracross brand, its products, its vision and mission. ? RELEVANT EXPERIENCE & SKILLS Bachelor\u2019s degree required; advanced degree considered a plus; 10+ years of senior level product marketing experience for SaaS products; Proven experience implementing new digital marketing strategies and leading the transformation of a legacy marketing organization to deliver best-practice digital marketing; High level of comfort working with marketing technology and analytics; able to make sense of data quickly and uses data to inform decisions and drive impact. Prior experience championing and leading the work to build a best-practice data analytics function from the top of the funnel to the bottom; Exceptional communication skills - must be able to articulate complex messaging in a clear, concise and \u2018plain English\u2019 manner both verbally and in writing; Charisma and energy and the ability to be a compelling and motivating brand champion internally and externally; Experience collaborating tightly with sales, finance, product development and services teams to achieve growth targets; demonstrable ability to communicate, present and influence key stakeholders at all levels of an organization; Deep understanding and experience with Salesforce.com and Hubspot; Prior experience integrating marketing teams from acquisitions; Excellent leadership and team building/management skills; ability to provide clear and concise direction/feedback to external and internal stakeholders as well as the ability to influence others; Team player with strong collaborative instincts who appropriately balances his or her contribution as both a functional leader and a strategic partner to peers with respect to articulating the greater company vision for integrated marketing solutions. Self-motivated and entrepreneurial; a leader as well as doer and a subject matter expert. A fit with Magnus/Veracross culture \u2013 someone that can be professional, down to earth, create trust, engaging, and likable. ? ",
